lead_paragraph: Pinch-hitter Matt den Dekker, recalled from the minors earlier in the day, had a tiebreaking, two-run double in a three-run seventh inning that led the Washington Nationals over the Atlanta Braves 3-1 Wednesday night for an opening two-game sweep.

headline.print_headline: Nationals Top Braves 3-1 on Den Dekker's 2-Run Double
